05:20.051 --> 05:22.051
...Norvis, Fucker,

05:22.053 --> 05:25.087
Bogdan, Juniper...

05:25.089 --> 05:29.058
Yeah, that's Pepsi,
Pongo, and God.

05:29.060 --> 05:31.596
And my mate, Guy Clinch.

05:33.731 --> 05:35.164
Nobility, he is.

05:35.166 --> 05:36.700
Yeah, he's like cousin
to the King

05:36.702 --> 05:38.068
or Queen or something.

05:38.070 --> 05:39.702
He had a bit of trouble
when he first come

05:39.704 --> 05:40.936
into the Black Cross,

05:40.938 --> 05:42.938
but I introduced him
to some faces

05:42.940 --> 05:44.911
and now he's got
a face all on his own.

05:46.611 --> 05:49.712
Guy Clinch, Samson Young.

05:49.714 --> 05:51.847
- Pleasure to meet you, Samson.
- Sam's fine.

05:51.849 --> 05:53.849
You know, Sam here
is newly arrived.

05:53.851 --> 05:55.652
American. Writer.

05:55.654 --> 05:57.988
Huh?

05:57.990 --> 06:00.323
Well, fuck me.

06:00.325 --> 06:02.959
- You all right, mon?
- Yeah, loan sharks.

06:02.961 --> 06:04.327
Loan sharks?

06:04.329 --> 06:06.096
Keith, you really
shouldn't be doing that.

06:06.098 --> 06:08.298
What? Eh? Every time
I borrowed money

06:08.300 --> 06:09.798
from you, I paid you back,
didn't I?

06:09.800 --> 06:11.704
Well, no. You've never
actually paid me back.

06:15.740 --> 06:16.739
Pleasure to meet you, Sam.

06:16.741 --> 06:18.674
Yeah, you too.

06:18.676 --> 06:21.645
Yeah, listen. You don't
loan money, do you, Sam, huh?

06:21.647 --> 06:24.013
No, I'm just a broke writer.

06:24.015 --> 06:26.618
Huh. Why should
they own me, right?

06:27.885 --> 06:28.853
Yeah.

06:31.188 --> 06:33.423
But I'm behind on me rent.

06:33.425 --> 06:35.024
Two fucking weeks.

06:35.026 --> 06:37.327
Listen, I appreciate
your trustworthy instincts.

06:37.329 --> 06:38.661
Yeah, right.

06:38.663 --> 06:39.695
<i>I had to borrow a pinch</i>

06:39.697 --> 06:41.197
<i>from me old loan shark,</i>

06:41.199 --> 06:42.368
<i>Kirk Stockist.</i>

06:43.368 --> 06:45.168
<i>Trouble was,
I already owed a ton</i>

06:45.170 --> 06:48.671
<i>for me darts training
and other expenses.</i>

06:48.673 --> 06:51.106
I recognize the stench
but not the face.

06:51.108 --> 06:53.676
<i>So then I had to
borrow money from Ashley Royal</i>

06:53.678 --> 06:55.445
<i>to pay the vig
on Kirk's loan.</i>

06:55.447 --> 06:56.949
You've got a week.

06:58.082 --> 06:59.448
Then you suffer.

06:59.450 --> 07:00.950
<i>Woulda been fine
had it not have been</i>

07:00.952 --> 07:02.786
<i>for an unwise investment.</i>

07:02.788 --> 07:04.354
So now I gotta borrow money

07:04.356 --> 07:06.826
from me old mate
Chick Purchase.

07:08.926 --> 07:11.928
<i>Trouble was, there's a bit
of bad blood between us.</i>

07:11.930 --> 07:12.965
You know something?

07:14.265 --> 07:17.299
I'm actually
fucking ecstatic

07:17.301 --> 07:19.004
to loan you
as much as I can.

07:19.937 --> 07:22.972
So that I can fuck you up
as hard as I can

07:22.974 --> 07:24.306
when you don't pay.

07:24.308 --> 07:26.743
Don't tickle me with that.

07:26.745 --> 07:28.243
And, love...

07:28.245 --> 07:30.746
it will not be
over quickly.

07:30.748 --> 07:32.414
And I promise,

07:32.416 --> 07:33.952
you will not enjoy it.

07:38.423 --> 07:40.893
So, my advice to you...

07:41.926 --> 07:44.029
is to celebrate
while you can...

07:47.332 --> 07:50.366
go and drop a bit
on a bird, eh?

07:50.368 --> 07:52.835
Now, all three
require payment,

07:52.837 --> 07:55.006
immediate and in full.

08:00.245 --> 08:01.380
Take care, love.

08:08.753 --> 08:10.155
You don't play darts,
do you, sir?

08:11.957 --> 08:13.291
I'll give you lessons
if you like.

08:14.760 --> 08:16.859
Darts...

08:16.861 --> 08:18.096
is destiny.

08:22.334 --> 08:23.803
<i>My God.</i>

08:51.396 --> 08:53.395
Do you have any
Gauloises cigarettes?

08:53.397 --> 08:55.999
We don't sell
French fags here, darling.

08:56.001 --> 08:57.299
Carlyle!

08:57.301 --> 08:58.802
Come here.

08:58.804 --> 09:00.102
Right.

09:00.104 --> 09:01.037
Now.

09:01.039 --> 09:02.271
Go and get this lady

09:02.273 --> 09:03.573
her French snouts, will ya?

09:03.575 --> 09:05.975
Go on. Fuck off.

09:05.977 --> 09:09.345
Poor grieving girl, eh?

09:09.347 --> 09:11.280
Is the world
against everything?

09:11.282 --> 09:13.249
I've lived down the road
for over a year now,

09:13.251 --> 09:15.321
and this is the first time
I've been in here.

09:16.320 --> 09:17.922
Always wondered
what it was like.

09:19.424 --> 09:20.925
Just never had the courage.

09:22.426 --> 09:24.360
I suppose this is...

09:24.362 --> 09:25.995
by way of having been
at a wake?

09:25.997 --> 09:28.130
Yeah. Weren't family,
was he?

09:28.132 --> 09:29.899
Not anyone I knew very well.

09:29.901 --> 09:31.303
Still. Does you credit.

09:32.204 --> 09:34.270
No, shows respect,
don't it?

09:34.272 --> 09:36.239
<i>Here we are
at the event horizon</i>

09:36.241 --> 09:37.810
<i>of a black hole.</i>

09:41.445 --> 09:43.847
<i>Anything, including
matter and photons,</i>

09:43.849 --> 09:46.484
<i>that pass this boundary
are unable to escape.</i>

09:50.188 --> 09:51.855
A black veil.

09:51.857 --> 09:53.358
It's ironic
how becoming it is.

09:54.859 --> 09:57.195
One never gets enough
opportunity to wear one.

09:58.128 --> 10:00.362
People should die
more often.

10:00.364 --> 10:02.300
What's your name,
sweetheart?

10:04.301 --> 10:06.202
Nicola Six.

10:06.204 --> 10:08.170
What? Sex? Huh.

10:08.172 --> 10:10.475
It's S-I-X.

10:17.616 --> 10:18.884
Fuck off.

10:21.185 --> 10:22.418
Thank you.

10:22.420 --> 10:24.287
Now, huh.

10:27.959 --> 10:29.992
An honor...

10:29.994 --> 10:31.930
to service you.

10:48.512 --> 10:49.581
You all right?

10:52.383 --> 10:53.348
Sorry.

10:53.350 --> 10:54.419
Thank you.

10:55.586 --> 10:56.921
I must be leaving now.

10:59.023 --> 11:00.191
You've been very kind.

11:05.063 --> 11:06.395
Keith...

11:06.397 --> 11:08.597
You're...
You're not, are you?

11:08.599 --> 11:10.165
A girl like that?

11:10.167 --> 11:11.400
A girl like what?

11:11.402 --> 11:14.370
- Well...
- Mate, she's dreaming of it.

11:14.372 --> 11:16.172
Yeah, she's begging for it.

11:16.174 --> 11:18.106
She's just been
to a funeral, Keith.

11:18.108 --> 11:19.578
Well, then
she's praying for it.

11:21.713 --> 11:24.480
Life fucking goes on,
don't it, eh?

11:24.482 --> 11:25.581
<i>With Keith and Guy,</i>

11:25.583 --> 11:28.217
<i>I had two promising
story characters.</i>

11:28.219 --> 11:30.555
<i>Two men forming
a social contrast.</i>

11:34.325 --> 11:37.028
<i>But none of this would have
started without the girl.</i>

11:43.468 --> 11:45.237
<i>There was no book
without the girl.</i>

11:50.575 --> 11:52.342
You know, they say
the first thing that will go

11:52.344 --> 11:54.246
with the hot sun
will be the flowers.

11:56.547 --> 11:58.349
Won't be any more flowers.

12:03.287 --> 12:05.454
Now, I see
a girl like you.

12:05.456 --> 12:07.323
You know, bit of a beauty.

12:07.325 --> 12:09.424
Head in the clouds, as such.

12:09.426 --> 12:12.462
Now, me? I'm Handy Andy.

12:12.464 --> 12:14.065
You know, I'm Mr. Fixit.

12:18.069 --> 12:20.502
So what's your
phone number, Nick?

12:20.504 --> 12:22.607
Of all things, she lives
in my building.

12:24.342 --> 12:25.276
Remarkable.

12:27.478 --> 12:29.412
<i>The pain kit
from Dr. Slizzard</i>

12:29.414 --> 12:31.246
<i>arrived in good time.</i>

12:31.248 --> 12:33.118
<i>Like a box of candy.</i>

12:38.455 --> 12:39.991
<i>Why can't I do it?</i>

12:40.691 --> 12:42.293
<i>Why can't I just write?</i>

12:45.397 --> 12:48.467
<i>I write. I'm a writer.</i>

14:15.719 --> 14:17.720
<i>From the moment
Nicola's thoughts began</i>

14:17.722 --> 14:19.454
<i>to be consecutive,</i>

14:19.456 --> 14:21.491
<i>she knew two strange things.</i>

14:21.493 --> 14:24.159
<i>I've always known
what was going to happen next.</i>

14:24.161 --> 14:26.462
<i>The second was that
she must never tell anyone</i>

14:26.464 --> 14:27.663
<i>about the first.</i>

14:27.665 --> 14:30.165
<i>Hers was a specific kind
of fortune telling.</i>

14:30.167 --> 14:33.870
<i>Nicola saw the death
of many, many things.</i>

14:33.872 --> 14:35.737
<i>She knew her young friend
Dominique</i>

14:35.739 --> 14:37.073
<i>would fall to her death.</i>

14:37.075 --> 14:41.309
<i>How painful. I was
prepared for Mom and Dad.</i>

14:41.311 --> 14:43.813
<i>She knew her parents
would die in a plane crash.</i>

14:43.815 --> 14:46.582
<i>They both died,
together,</i>

14:46.584 --> 14:48.885
<i>as I always knew they would.</i>

14:48.887 --> 14:50.488
<i>So why love anyone?</i>

14:53.190 --> 14:55.560
<i>I met the surviving
pilot and slept with him.</i>

14:56.860 --> 14:59.430
<i>If the crash didn't
kill him, love would.</i>

15:00.297 --> 15:03.632
<i>She saw the circles
of concentric devastation</i>

15:03.634 --> 15:06.871
<i>with London like a bull's-eye
in the center of the board.</i>

15:09.474 --> 15:11.175
<i>She knew that was coming.</i>

15:12.243 --> 15:14.713
<i>Nicola knew when
her own story ended, too.</i>

15:15.780 --> 15:17.882
<i>Some minutes after midnight...</i>

15:18.849 --> 15:20.853
<i>on her 30th birthday.</i>

15:21.886 --> 15:23.454
<i>Guy Fawkes Day.</i>

15:24.789 --> 15:26.325
<i>Her final entry.</i>

15:27.658 --> 15:29.592
<i>"In the Black Cross Pub."</i>

15:29.594 --> 15:31.360
<i>I found my murderer.</i>

15:31.362 --> 15:32.595
<i>"I found my murderer."</i>

15:32.597 --> 15:33.665
<i>I met him.</i>

15:34.599 --> 15:35.566
"Today."

15:45.576 --> 15:46.909
- Yes?
- Oh, hello.

15:46.911 --> 15:48.778
Uh, my name
is Samson Young.

15:48.780 --> 15:50.612
I live downstairs.

15:50.614 --> 15:51.582
Um...

16:09.300 --> 16:10.301
Are you gonna sit down?

16:12.502 --> 16:13.638
Thank you.

16:18.810 --> 16:19.844
Okay.

16:21.945 --> 16:24.382
So I, uh,
I read everything.

16:25.950 --> 16:26.951
Look...

16:28.485 --> 16:29.420
I'm a writer.

16:30.854 --> 16:31.956
Anything I might know?

16:33.523 --> 16:34.959
I seriously doubt it.

16:37.695 --> 16:40.799
Listen. I believe
your premonitions.

16:44.401 --> 16:45.937
I believe you see
your death.

16:51.642 --> 16:53.311
So who's going to kill you?

16:56.781 --> 16:57.782
I don't know.

17:00.951 --> 17:02.954
I just know
he was there yesterday.

17:08.959 --> 17:11.893
I've always wanted to write
a murder novel, but I...

17:11.895 --> 17:14.632
was never close
enough to it. I...

17:15.666 --> 17:20.035
Um... I-I believe
I would have to be there,

17:20.037 --> 17:21.440
recording it.

17:22.873 --> 17:24.008
Would you let me do that?

17:25.476 --> 17:27.378
I think you could be
my masterpiece.

17:32.784 --> 17:33.752
Yes.

17:48.865 --> 17:50.368
I know what you're thinking.

17:51.102 --> 17:52.470
It's a gift.

17:53.603 --> 17:55.007
And I'm going to take it.

17:56.373 --> 17:57.608
Regardless.

17:59.009 --> 18:00.945
<i>She was a great character.</i>

18:01.912 --> 18:03.614
<i>A fascinating creature.</i>

18:07.517 --> 18:08.487
<i>Compelling.</i>

18:09.687 --> 18:10.889
<i>Self-destructive.</i>

18:14.892 --> 18:15.925
<i>I had the makings</i>

18:15.927 --> 18:17.963
<i>of a really snappy
little thriller.</i>

18:36.447 --> 18:38.050
<i>She entered the Black Cross.</i>

18:39.517 --> 18:42.150
<i>She entered the pub
and its murk.</i>

18:42.152 --> 18:45.420
<i>She lifted her veil
with both hands like a bride.</i>

18:45.422 --> 18:47.890
<i>Surveyed the main actors
of the scene,</i>

18:47.892 --> 18:50.692
<i>and immediately
she knew, with pain,</i>

18:50.694 --> 18:52.630
<i>within intense recognition,</i>

18:53.564 --> 18:56.564
<i>that she had found him,
her murderer.</i>

18:56.566 --> 18:58.002
I just had a deja vu.

19:01.905 --> 19:04.707
<i>Nicola awoke
and heard the rain</i>

19:04.709 --> 19:06.809
<i>and went back to sleep again.</i>

19:06.811 --> 19:07.976
<i>Or she tried.</i>

19:10.547 --> 19:11.714
<i>I want more</i>

19:11.716 --> 19:14.015
<i>of that Mark Asprey.</i>

19:14.017 --> 19:15.985
<i>That's what I want more of.</i>

19:15.987 --> 19:17.686
